I can't possibly imagine what possible connection the quote<br>
of Samuel Adams has with the Vietnam War. We invaded a small<br>
distant country that had absolutely nothing to do with us, <br>
and delibrately slaughtered two million people. Our government killed 57,600 of its own citizens by sending them <br>
over there. The American government did not want democracy<br>
in Vietnam. It wanted to establish a puppet government <br>
controlled by Washington. What does that have to do with <br>
&quot;liberty&quot;? Some people posting on this board seem to be <br>
blaming others for not wanting to die. What percentage of<br>
the human population of the planet doesn't want to die?<br>
Is this something you can blame someone for? How can you <br>
blame someone for choosing to not put himself in harm's way?<br>
If these people believe that it is a bad thing, a sign of <br>
weakness, to not want to die, then what prevents them from <br>
jumping in front of trains? 
